{"type":"text","timestamp":1775846836790,"sessionID":"ses_2874e29eaffetVEB9ua4aKG6a7","part":{"id":"prt_d78b832ea0017ftr0iN2ZRK0yN","messageID":"msg_d78b81184001eL0UIWMBmJFKmM","sessionID":"ses_2874e29eaffetVEB9ua4aKG6a7","type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. Let me provide a summary:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've implemented the **Sandbox GC (Garbage Collection)定时清理机制** for the `pkg/workloadmanager` module as specified in AR-008.\n\n### Files Created:\n\n1. **`pkg/workloadmanager/gc.go`** - Complete GC implementation with:\n   - `GCConfig` struct (GCEnabled, GCInterval, GCBatchSize)\n   - `GCWorker` - Periodic garbage collection using time.Ticker\n   - Expiration detection using existing `expiration.go` functions\n   - Resource cleanup (Services, ConfigMaps, PVCs) using existing `cleanup.go`\n   - Force deletion (GracePeriodSeconds=0) for stale sandboxes\n   - PVC retention policy check for Retain PVs\n   - Comprehensive logging of GC cycles and cleanup details\n   - `GCHandler` for manual GC trigger, status, and config updates\n\n2. **`pkg/workloadmanager/gc_test.go`** - Comprehensive unit tests (28 test cases):\n   - GCConfig validation\n   - GCWorker lifecycle (start/stop/running state)\n   - Expiration detection for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n   - State detection (Unknown/Running/Failed/Deleting)\n   - Last activity time parsing\n   - GCHandler methods\n   - GCResult and GCStats structures\n\n### Acceptance Criteria Met:\n- ✅ GC starts automatically when enabled (default: 5 min interval)\n- ✅ GC can be disabled via configuration\n- ✅ GC interval configurable\n- ✅ Graceful shutdown\n- ✅ All 4 expiration types detected (TTL, idle, max lifetime, stale)\n- ✅ Force deletion for stale sandboxes\n- ✅ Orphaned K8s resources cleaned up\n- ✅ PVCs with Retain policy skipped\n- ✅ GC cycle results logged","time":{"start":1775846836787,"end":1775846836787}}}
